---
title: Sizzling Beef Stir-Fry over Jasmine Rice
description: Stir-fries are a handy dish for weeknights because you can get them on the table quickly with minimal fuss. Just prep your protein and veg, whip together a simple sauce, and let those ingredients sizzle in the pan. For this version, we’re tossing beef cubes, bell pepper, and bok choy in a marinade of ginger, garlic, and soy sauce. It’s simple yet tremendously satisfying.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/beef-and-garlic-sizzle-stir-fry-a7911f84.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/beef-and-garlic-sizzle-stir-fry-8d1b3fc2.pdf
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/beef-and-garlic-sizzle-stir-fry-582c27ce5ca1530d2f7e4e52
time required: 30 minutes
course: main course
cuisine: Asian
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 545 kcal
  fat: 13 g
  saturated fat: 3 g
  carbohydrates: 56 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 44 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1103 mg
---

Bring 1 cup water to a boil in a #small pot{}. When boiling, add @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}. Cover, reduce to a simmer, and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Keep covered.

Wash and dry all produce. Meanwhile, halve, peel, and thinly slice @Red Onion{1}. Core, seed, and thinly slice @Red Bell Pepper{1}. Trim and quarter @Baby Bok Choy{2}, then separate leaves. Mince or grate @Garlic{2%clove}. Peel and mince @Ginger{1%thumb}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine ginger, garlic, @Soy Sauce{4%unit}, @Sugar{2%teaspoon}, and a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon}. Add @Beef Sirloin Tips{12%ounce} and toss to coat. Season with @Salt{unit} and @Pepper{unit}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak tips and toss until browned and cooked to desired doneness, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and onion. Cook, tossing, until just tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add bok choy to pan and toss until tender, another ~{2-3%minutes}. (TIP: If veggies won't soften, add a splash of water.) Season with salt and pepper.

Return beef to pan and toss to heat through. Serve stir-fry on a bed of rice.